  "text": "RF did not bring about any change in the weight of healthy male adolescents. It seems unlikely that the retained Ben Fraj et al 7 adolescents were dehydrated. Conclusions about the effects of RF on healthy adolescent weight were controversial. While some studies reported no significant change in weight during Ramadan ,6,21,24 another one detected weight gains during the second week of Ramadan (47.0 ± 3.4 kg) compared with Before-R (45.4 ± 3.2 kg). 22 A study performed during Ramadan 2010 has described the effects of RF on weight in 18 Muslim boys aged 9 to 15 years. [CITATION_1] The weight of the nine pubescent boys increased significantly in the fourth week of Ramadan (55.4 ± 11.0 kg) compared with Before-R (53.9 ± 10.5 kg), and the first week of Ramadan (54.6 ± 10.8 kg).",
